Zola Majavu returns to the Premier Soccer League. BackpagePix/Samuel Shivambu JOHANNESBURG - The Premier Soccer League has brought advocate Zola Majavu back into the fold. This as the league looks to strengthen its prosecutions department. Majavu will be the PSL’s new prosecutor after Michael Murphy reportedly resigned shortly after prosecutor Nande Becker left the organisation. "Yes, he's now a member of the prosecution of the PSL going forward for now," said Irvin Khoza, PSL chairperson.